2000-12-05  Gary Granger  <granger@ale.atd.ucar.edu>

	* Moved the gp ui require function to the library and use it in dm
	  and dsDaemon, allowing more config files to be moved into the
	  library and allowing configuration files to be more easily
	  shared between among projects.

	* Add a FieldSelect widget to the graphics process which can be
	  popped up with the 'selectfield' ui command and from FieldMenu.
	  Both FieldMenu and selectfield share a common spec string,
	  passed in the FieldMenu parameter value or as the selectfield
	  argument, which sets options like the field parameter to change
	  or the field select command to use.

	* Add the IconBar.sh script to the dm library.  It can be used by
	  a project to generate the usual iconbar boilerplate to which can
	  be added only the parts unique to a project.
	
	* Change the add-data-command approach for some of the window
	  templates, where the add command pops up a widget which provides
	  the options for adding a particular platform.  Components for
	  the templates are taken from the -components.pd files.  The
	  xygraph modules can now control more of the axes and side
	  annotation parameters.
	
1999-11-23  Gary Granger  <granger@ale.atd.ucar.edu>

	* Developments in the Archiver and ingest scheduler (is) programs
	  for the Integrated Sounding System have been merged back into
	  Zebra.  Both can now run in the background without an X display
	  or terminal.  An X interface for the Archiver can be opened on
	  any X display, even after the Archiver has been started in the
	  background.  The ingest scheduler supports the 'zrun' command
	  protocol so that UI commands can be sent to is from any
	  terminal.

