Tue Nov 26 14:00:33 1996  Gary Granger  <granger@narnia.atd.ucar.edu>

	* config.h: critical parameters have been reconciled between ARM
	  and RDP.  Field name/desc/units lengths increased to ARM limit,
	  platform name length decreased to save space while still longer
	  than any name ever used, and filename length increased to at
	  least ARM limit.  These changes, along with cleaner and
	  non-automatic bad value handling mentioned below, should keep
	  Zebra compatible between both ARM and RDP installations without
	  recompiling.

	* DataStore: netCDF i/o tries to closely match datachunk and file:
	  all automatic attributes missing_value, units, and long_name,
	  are only added to the file if non-existent in the datachunk;
	  when reading, global and field bad value attributes are only set
	  in the datachunk if they exist in the file; no filling occurs
	  unless requesting a non-existent field or explicitly requested
	  in the details

